<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 2:17PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Hempstead,
northeastern Miller, north central Lafayette and Nevada Counties
through 300 PM CDT...
At 217 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fulton, or 10 miles southwest of Hope, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hope, Prescott, Emmet, Perrytown, Rosston, Fulton, Willisville,
Bodcaw, Cale, McNab, Patmos, Oakhaven, Young, Sutton, Waterloo,
Boughton, Mount Moriah, Hervey, Morris and Laneburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
